14. Liberum patrem, etc. Dionysus, according to one legend (Plut. Quaest. Gr. 56). pursued the Amazons from Ephe- sus to Samos and there slew them; ac- cording to another (Diod. 3. 71, etc.), united with them against the Titans. The legend of Amazons in Western Asia is found in Homer (11. 3, 1893 6, 186). Pindar, according to Pausanias (7. 2, 7), ascribed to them the foundation of the Ephesian temple ; another legend (see 4. 56, 1) makes an Amazon foundress of Smyrna. The Attic legend respecting them (Hdt. 9. 27, 5, etc.) is famous from its representations in art.
